    "description": "StrategyCorp canonical product categorization taxonomy — 5-level hierarchy. Defines how raw bank product codes should be classified into Lines of Business, Product Types, Categories, Sub-categories, and Special designations.",
    "notes": [
      "Levels 1–3 (Line of Business, Type, Category) are StrategyCorp-defined and canonical across all FIs.",
      "Levels 4–5 (Sub-category, Special) are FI-configurable — each bank customizes these to mirror their internal nomenclature.",
      "All level names are dynamic (<N>) so the user can rename them in the UI to match their bank's terminology.",
      "The taxonomy is delivered as an editable template so eligible users can add/change categories.",
      "Retail and Business share some Category values (Checking, Savings, CDs) but diverge in Loans and Services.",
      "Business includes Cash Management Services (AKA Treasury Management) with ~20 specialized service categories.",
      "Wealth Management is a standalone LoB with Securities and Cash Management sub-structures.",
      "When the model cannot confidently classify a product code, it should flag it for manual review — never force-fit.",
      "The target Silver table is product_type_configuration_master."
    ]
  },

