  "classification_rules": [
    "First determine Line of Business (Retail, Business, or Wealth Management) using customer class codes (CFCLAS) and product context.",
    "Then classify the Product Type (Deposits, Loans, Services, Securities, Cash Management Services).",
    "Then determine the Category (Level 3) within the Product Type.",
    "Sub-category and Special (Levels 4–5) are FI-configurable — propose when raw data provides enough context, otherwise leave blank.",
    "Use Purpose Codes (PURCOD) to distinguish consumer (01, 02) vs business (03-06, 09) vs other loan types.",
    "Public Funds accounts are ambiguous — could be Retail or Business depending on FI convention.",
    "Wealth Management has its own deposit and loan products (Securities > Transaction, Securities > Loans) — do not confuse with Retail/Business.",
    "Cash Management Services (Treasury) only applies to Business LoB — these are operational services, not deposit/loan products.",
    "When the model cannot confidently classify, flag for manual review — never force-fit into a wrong category."
  ]
